.TH smi-jail-update "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Jail Command"
.SH NAME
smi-jail-update \- Update one or more FreeBSD jails
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-jail-update
.I JAIL_NAME...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-jail-update
performs a comprehensive update of the specified FreeBSD \fIJAIL_NAME\fR(s).
The update process includes both the base operating system and the installed packages within each jail.
.PP
For each jail, the following commands are executed:
.IP 1.
\fBfreebsd-update fetch\fR (Base system)
.IP 2.
\fBfreebsd-update install\fR (Base system)
.IP 3.
\fBpkg update -f\fR (Package repository)
.IP 4.
\fBpkg upgrade -y\fR (Installed packages)
.PP
The script ensures it is running as root (re-executes with \fBsudo\fR if necessary) and uses \fBchroot\fR(8) contexts for the updates.
